      "writtenOn": "2026-06-17T16:36:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is going to get called once per second by analyze(), right?\n\nWe should not be polling the D-Bus property value. This is going to cause a lot of expensive D-Bus traffic.\n\nFrom the commit comments, I thought the plan was to remove the Chassis object completely if it is not present.\n\nIf I misunderstood and the Chassis object will remain, then it should have an isPresent data member. That should be set and updated using the normal D-Bus pattern of\n- Get the D-Bus property value during initialization if it is available on D-Bus\n- Add an InterfacesAdded listener to cover case where property is published on D-Bus later\n- Add a PropertiesChanged listener for when the value changes",
      "revId": "49fe9a7d737a3347db698eec54e8efa8411134ea",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
