      "writtenOn": "2026-06-17T16:36:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You don\u0027t have to change this, but there is a newer way to handle the situation where a data member initially has no value.\n\nYou can use a std::optional\u003cuint64_t\u003e to represent two possible states:\n* Undefined value (I don\u0027t know the position value)\n* Defined value (e.g. 1-8 or whatever)\n\ne.g.\n```\n  std::optional\u003cuint64_t\u003e chassisPathPositionId;\n  \n  ...\n  \n  if (chassisPathPositionId)\n  {\n    // ... some code that only should happen if the position is defined/known\n  }\n```",
      "revId": "49fe9a7d737a3347db698eec54e8efa8411134ea",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
